Is this from the restaurant we went to?

467
00:45:25.682 --> 00:45:27.976 line:80%
Nothing gets past your tastebuds.

468
00:45:29.394 --> 00:45:31.187 line:80%
After the restaurant was gone,

469
00:45:31.271 --> 00:45:34.399 line:80%
I looked for restaurants
that made it like them.

470
00:45:34.482 --> 00:45:36.985 line:80%
I couldn't find anything similar.

471
00:45:37.068 --> 00:45:40.905 line:80%
I was like, "It's Busan!
Why can't these restaurants make it?"

472
00:45:44.325 --> 00:45:46.369 line:80%
"Why are they all different?" And...

473
00:45:49.372 --> 00:45:53.835 line:80%
You don't have to gobble it up.
You can eat it whenever you want now.

474
00:45:56.796 --> 00:46:00.758 line:80%
They opened a branch in Seoul.
Just five minutes from here.

475
00:46:05.847 --> 00:46:06.764 line:80%
No way...

476
00:46:07.891 --> 00:46:12.562 line:80%
I thought of stopping the redevelopment.
But this method was much easier.

477
00:46:13.646 --> 00:46:15.273 line:80%
That's okay, right?

478
00:46:20.653 --> 00:46:22.155 line:80%
Aren't you so impressed?

479
00:46:22.906 --> 00:46:26.451 line:80%
No, I was thinking about telling you
what I want to eat next.

480
00:46:26.534 --> 00:46:27.535 line:80%
What?

481
00:46:27.619 --> 00:46:29.496 line:80%
I was just kidding.

482
00:46:29.579 --> 00:46:32.165 line:80%
Thank you so much.

483
00:46:32.248 --> 00:46:33.541 line:80%
Eat slowly.

484
00:46:33.625 --> 00:46:35.084 line:80%
I'll eat it every day.

485
00:46:35.627 --> 00:46:36.836 line:80%
It's so good.

486
00:46:39.130 --> 00:46:40.465 line:80%
Right, Ji-hyuk.

487
00:46:41.424 --> 00:46:43.343 line:80%
What are you doing this weekend?

488
00:46:44.511 --> 00:46:46.596 line:80%
I want to go somewhere with you.

489
00:47:12.580 --> 00:47:18.002 line:80%
When I was young,
I always felt anxious and lonely.

490
00:47:20.380 --> 00:47:21.381 line:80%
But...

491
00:47:23.216 --> 00:47:27.095 line:80%
I'm not anxious or lonely anymore.

492
00:47:31.391 --> 00:47:33.268 line:80%
Since I have you beside me.

493
00:47:36.396 --> 00:47:38.356 line:80%
It's no surprise.

494
00:47:38.439 --> 00:47:41.442 line:80%
I'm the best allowance your dad picked
to give you.

495
00:47:48.741 --> 00:47:49.742 line:80%
This...

496
00:47:51.578 --> 00:47:53.705 line:80%
is where we started.

497
00:47:58.042 --> 00:48:00.545 line:80%
I want to start our new start here too.

498
00:48:10.346 --> 00:48:11.347 line:80%
Ji-hyuk.

499
00:48:16.352 --> 00:48:19.772 line:80%
Will you marry me?

500
00:48:35.705 --> 00:48:37.165 line:80%
I can't believe you.

501
00:48:44.881 --> 00:48:46.090 line:80%
No, I mean...

502
00:48:47.467 --> 00:48:50.053 line:80%
That's just how I feel now.

503
00:48:50.136 --> 00:48:53.640 line:80%
You don't have to give me an answer now.

504
00:48:53.723 --> 00:48:56.601 line:80%
How could you just leave like that?

505
00:48:56.684 --> 00:49:01.606 line:80%
I thought everything was back,
but he's still himself.

506
00:49:10.281 --> 00:49:11.949 line:80%
You can do whatever you want

507
00:49:13.117 --> 00:49:14.577 line:80%
but not a proposal.

508
00:49:34.055 --> 00:49:36.057 line:80%
I've been carrying it for so long.

509
00:49:39.143 --> 00:49:41.521 line:80%
I wanted to propose all this time.

510
00:49:54.325 --> 00:49:55.326 line:80%
Wil you...

511
00:50:00.206 --> 00:50:01.416 line:80%
marry me?

512
00:50:49.672 --> 00:50:53.050 line:80%
Of course,
there are things that didn't change.

513
00:50:53.134 --> 00:50:55.303 line:80%
A BETTER TOMORROW, CORRECTION OF HOPE

514
00:50:55.386 --> 00:50:57.096 line:80%
I don't know why.

515
00:50:59.724 --> 00:51:01.434 line:80%
Why Ji-won wants

516
00:51:02.351 --> 00:51:07.064 line:80%
to take everything I have.
Why she wants me to be miserable.

517
00:51:07.690 --> 00:51:09.776 line:80%
It's because you're too nice.

518
00:51:10.318 --> 00:51:13.529 line:80%
People like her only go after nice people.

519
00:51:13.613 --> 00:51:14.864 line:80%
You have to nip them

520
00:51:15.740 --> 00:51:16.824 line:80%
in the bud.

521
00:51:18.075 --> 00:51:20.244 line:80%
How could a person do that?

522
00:51:21.162 --> 00:51:24.248 line:80%
I could endure all of that.

523
00:51:24.916 --> 00:51:25.917 line:80%
However...

524
00:51:28.127 --> 00:51:29.796 line:80%
Do you remember

525
00:51:32.006 --> 00:51:35.301 line:80%
when I told you
about Ji-won being delusional?

526
00:51:36.427 --> 00:51:38.971 line:80%
She kept saying I was gaslighting her.

527
00:51:39.055 --> 00:51:42.183 line:80%
That I was harassing her
and ruining her life.

528
00:51:42.266 --> 00:51:44.310 line:80%
She acted like a victim,

529
00:51:44.393 --> 00:51:46.479 line:80%
and that's why I ended up here.

530
00:51:46.562 --> 00:51:49.565 line:80%
Goodness, not only is she crazy,

531
00:51:49.649 --> 00:51:51.567 line:80%
she's also so pathetic.

532
00:51:52.401 --> 00:51:53.611 line:80%
I know, right?

533
00:51:54.821 --> 00:51:56.364 line:80%
But what can I do?

534
00:51:56.447 --> 00:51:59.325 line:80%
I'm her only friend.

535
00:51:59.408 --> 00:52:01.410 line:80%
I'll talk to her when I get out.

536
00:52:06.791 --> 00:52:08.209 line:80%
Inmate 2574, visitor.

537
00:52:14.674 --> 00:52:16.217 line:80%
Why are you so surprised?

538
00:52:22.640 --> 00:52:23.641 line:80%
You...

539
00:52:31.232 --> 00:52:32.817 line:80%
You didn't die?

540
00:52:32.900 --> 00:52:35.611 line:80%
I did. That's why I'm here.

541
00:52:40.032 --> 00:52:40.992 line:80%
One billion won.

542
00:52:42.159 --> 00:52:46.205 line:80%
Now that I'm dead, the benefit
of one billion won will be paid.

543
00:52:49.625 --> 00:52:50.835 line:80%
Can you...

544
00:52:52.628 --> 00:52:54.088 line:80%
give this to Ji-won?

545
00:52:57.592 --> 00:52:58.634 line:80%
What?

546
00:53:02.305 --> 00:53:03.598 line:80%
No.

547
00:53:04.432 --> 00:53:06.058 line:80%
Why is it Ji-won again?

548
00:53:06.142 --> 00:53:08.644 line:80%
-I'll kill her!
-
Executive Director Yu Ji-hyuk,

549
00:53:08.728 --> 00:53:11.105 line:80%
the grandson of U&K Group's Chairman Yu,

550
00:53:11.188 --> 00:53:14.358 line:80%
-is getting married at Winton Hotel.
-I only had Ji-won!

551
00:53:14.442 --> 00:53:16.444 line:80%
She felt the same!

552
00:53:16.527 --> 00:53:19.447 line:80%
I only had Ji-won!

553
00:53:19.530 --> 00:53:20.740 line:80%
Quiet!

554
00:53:21.449 --> 00:53:23.701 line:80%
Ma'am, please let me go! Please!

555
00:53:24.285 --> 00:53:26.162 line:80%
Let me out of here! Please!

556
00:53:28.915 --> 00:53:30.499 line:80%
Ji-won can't be happy.

557
00:53:31.083 --> 00:53:34.712 line:80%
She can't be happy without me!

558
00:53:34.795 --> 00:53:36.339 line:80%
She can't!

559
00:53:48.768 --> 00:53:51.145 line:80%
WEDDING
YU JI-HYUK, KANG JI-WON

560
00:55:12.560 --> 00:55:14.854 line:80%
Here come the bride and groom.

561
00:56:27.927 --> 00:56:30.137 line:80%
Everything got a little better.

562
00:56:30.846 --> 00:56:32.681 line:80%
I believe that.

563
00:57:09.426 --> 00:57:11.595 line:80%
I wish you were here.

564
00:57:14.014 --> 00:57:18.352 line:80%
You would be so happy
to see me this happy.

565
00:57:22.731 --> 00:57:24.650 line:80%
Hey. You all came too.

566
00:57:25.693 --> 00:57:28.070 line:80%
No, we didn't come.

567
00:57:29.947 --> 00:57:32.449 line:80%
I paid a lot for her congratulatory gift.

568
00:57:32.533 --> 00:57:33.909 line:80%
I applauded a lot too.

569
00:57:34.743 --> 00:57:36.287 line:80%
But I didn't eat anything.

570
00:57:41.167 --> 00:57:44.253 line:80%
The more I think about it,
the sorrier I feel.

571
00:57:44.336 --> 00:57:46.589 line:80%
And I truly hope she's happy.

572
00:57:48.632 --> 00:57:51.594 line:80%
But that's the only thing I can do.

573
00:57:52.136 --> 00:57:53.470 line:80%
You truly regret it.

574
00:57:56.932 --> 00:57:59.268 line:80%
One, two, three.

575
00:57:59.351 --> 00:58:02.021 line:80%
Dad, are you watching?

576
00:58:06.150 --> 00:58:06.984 line:80%
Let's go!

577
00:58:11.405 --> 00:58:13.949 line:80%
-Let's go!
-Let's go!

578
00:58:32.676 --> 00:58:36.597 line:80%
APRIL 2016

579
00:58:42.061 --> 00:58:47.942 line:80%
Hello, I'm Kang Ji-won, the director
of U&K's Second Chance Foundation.

580
00:58:50.653 --> 00:58:53.697 line:80%
Our foundation's planning
to gradually contribute

581
00:58:53.781 --> 00:58:57.785 line:80%
20 billion won through
major affiliated companies by next year.

582
00:58:58.744 --> 00:58:59.912 line:80%
From there,

583
00:58:59.995 --> 00:59:04.667 line:80%
U&K plans to initiate systematic
and continuous donations to the society

584
00:59:04.750 --> 00:59:08.379 line:80%
as a company that understands
the meaning of sharing.

585
00:59:11.298 --> 00:59:15.886 line:80%
Even in moments
when everything seems to be over,

586
00:59:16.553 --> 00:59:18.889 line:80%
I believe there's another path.

587
00:59:19.932 --> 00:59:21.934 line:80%
That path could even be better.

588
00:59:25.562 --> 00:59:28.023 line:80%
There must be a second chance.

589
00:59:28.107 --> 00:59:30.442 line:80%
No, it must be given.

590
00:59:30.526 --> 00:59:34.321 line:80%
To those suffering
because of one wrong choice they made,

591
00:59:34.405 --> 00:59:38.909 line:80%
I hope our foundation can be of help.

592
00:59:40.786 --> 00:59:41.704 line:80%
Thank you.

593
00:59:54.049 --> 00:59:56.635 line:80%
I'm doing well this time, right?

594
00:59:58.554 --> 00:59:59.430 line:80%
But...

595
00:59:59.513 --> 01:00:03.851 line:80%
OCTOBER 2017

596
01:00:24.997 --> 01:00:27.458 line:80%
Do babies really not sleep like this?

597
01:00:30.794 --> 01:00:31.879 line:80%
Ji-won.

598
01:00:32.880 --> 01:00:35.049 line:80%
Seeing the baby cry like this,

599
01:00:35.549 --> 01:00:38.302 line:80%
I think he's sick.
Let's take him to the hospital.

600
01:00:39.178 --> 01:00:40.220 line:80%
Let me see.

601
01:00:44.933 --> 01:00:46.268 line:80%
He's fine.

602
01:00:50.898 --> 01:00:52.149 line:80%
He pooped.

603
01:01:01.575 --> 01:01:03.202 line:80%
-Number two.
-He pooped a lot.

604
01:01:03.285 --> 01:01:04.203 line:80%
Hurry.

605
01:01:08.957 --> 01:01:10.667 line:80%
Why won't you sleep?

606
01:01:11.543 --> 01:01:13.587 line:80%
Did you poop?

607
01:01:13.670 --> 01:01:16.215 line:80%
Daddy will change your diaper.

608
01:01:16.298 --> 01:01:19.635 line:80%
I've never done this before,
so it's not easy.

609
01:01:19.718 --> 01:01:21.804 line:80%
But I think I'm doing a good job.

610
01:01:38.737 --> 01:01:43.117 line:80%
I am definitely moving forward
little by little now.

611
01:01:45.828 --> 01:01:50.249 line:80%
I'm not walking in place.
I'm walking forward.

612
01:01:56.588 --> 01:01:58.757 line:80%
I want to be land.

613
01:01:58.841 --> 01:02:01.051 line:80%
I want to be land.

614
01:02:01.135 --> 01:02:04.430 line:80%
-What are they saying?
-What? Land? Lamb?

615
01:02:05.514 --> 01:02:07.891 line:80%
But why does it sound familiar?

616
01:02:07.975 --> 01:02:10.018 line:80%
Where are our mom and dad?

617
01:02:11.353 --> 01:02:14.398 line:80%
I don't know.
They said it was their anniversary.

618
01:02:14.481 --> 01:02:17.067 line:80%
A super important
and once-only anniversary.

619
01:02:18.694 --> 01:02:19.570 line:80%
Grandfather.

620
01:02:21.905 --> 01:02:24.450 line:80%
So you can play with your aunt!

621
01:02:30.205 --> 01:02:31.206 line:80%
Come here!

622
01:02:31.832 --> 01:02:32.833 line:80%
This way!

623
01:02:33.834 --> 01:02:35.752 line:80%
Grandfather, save us!

624
01:02:35.836 --> 01:02:36.962 line:80%
Help us!

625
01:02:37.045 --> 01:02:39.965 line:80%
OUR FAMILY MOTTO:
BECOME EACH OTHER'S STURDY LAND!

626
01:02:40.048 --> 01:02:41.467 line:80%
I WANT TO BE LAND!

627
01:02:41.550 --> 01:02:48.015 line:80%
APRIL 12, 2023

628
01:02:59.443 --> 01:03:04.490 line:80%
And today is the day that all the seasons
I have spent before ended.

629
01:03:06.241 --> 01:03:11.121 line:80%
I can't believe I can spend
the same season so differently like this.

630
01:03:21.048 --> 01:03:22.799 line:80%
This is the middle of spring.

631
01:03:26.803 --> 01:03:28.305 line:80%
It's beautiful.

632
01:03:29.515 --> 01:03:32.100 line:80%
I've always liked this artist.

633
01:03:32.184 --> 01:03:35.103 line:80%
But I think the painting style
has changed a bit.

634
01:03:35.896 --> 01:03:39.650 line:80%
The painter worked so hard
until the work was acknowledged.

635
01:03:41.151 --> 01:03:44.613 line:80%
Thanks to our foundation,
the painter could work at ease.

636
01:03:46.156 --> 01:03:48.033 line:80%
It's back to normal now.

637
01:03:49.159 --> 01:03:50.994 line:80%
This was how it should've been.

638
01:03:52.371 --> 01:03:56.291 line:80%
It could've been this beautiful.

639
01:03:58.210 --> 01:04:02.297 line:80%
I'm living properly now, Dad.

640
01:04:10.347 --> 01:04:11.348 line:80%
Thank you.

641
01:04:15.435 --> 01:04:17.437 line:80%
For making April 12, 2023

642
01:04:19.314 --> 01:04:21.191 line:80%
a completely different day.

643
01:04:27.698 --> 01:04:28.907 line:80%
Thank you...

644
01:04:33.203 --> 01:04:36.248 line:80%
for making me look forward to tomorrow.

645
01:05:03.984 --> 01:05:05.319 line:80%
I'm so happy.

646
01:07:07.399 --> 01:07:09.401 line:80%
Translated by Suyun Mounce

